  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're going through this situation. Navigating feelings when your best friend is dating someone you have a crush on can be challenging and emotionally complex. Here are some steps you might consider to help manage your feelings and maintain healthy relationships:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings:**\n   - It's important to recognize and validate your emotions. Feeling hurt, jealous, or confused is natural in this scenario.\n\n2. **Reflect on Your Emotions:**\n   - Take some time to understand why you have feelings for your crush. Is it genuine affection, attraction, or perhaps something else? Understanding your emotions can help you decide how to proceed.\n\n3. **Assess the Friendship:**\n   - Consider how important your friendship is to you. If maintaining the friendship is a priority, you might choose to set aside your romantic feelings to preserve the relationship.\n\n4. **Communicate with Your Best Friend:**\n   - If you feel comfortable, have an open and honest conversation with your friend. Share your feelings without pressuring them or making them feel guilty. Clear communication can prevent misunderstandings and help maintain trust.\n\n5. **Respect Their Relationship:**\n   - It's crucial to respect your friend's relationship with your crush. Trying to interfere can harm your friendship and create tension within your social circle.\n\n6. **Focus on Self-Care:**\n   - Engage in activities that make you happy and help you relax. Surround yourself with supportive people, and consider pursuing hobbies or interests that can divert your mind from the situation.\n\n7. **Seek Support:**\n   - Talking to other friends, family members, or a counselor can provide you with additional perspectives and emotional support.\n\n8. **Consider Your Options:**\n   - If, after some time, you realize that your feelings are too strong to manage, you might decide to distance yourself temporarily to heal and gain clarity.\n\n9. **Maintain Healthy Boundaries:**\n   - Setting boundaries can help you navigate interactions with both your friend and your crush without overstepping or causing discomfort.\n\n10. **Stay Open to Future Possibilities:**\n    - Relationships and feelings can evolve over time. Stay open to the possibility that circumstances might change, allowing for different dynamics in the future.\n\nRemember, it's okay to feel conflicted in this situation. Taking care of your emotional well-being and maintaining honesty in your relationships will help you navigate this challenging experience. If you find it difficult to cope, seeking professional support from a counselor or therapist can provide valuable guidance.",
